The recursive solutions are OK, the only small issue is that they return a superset of declared and inherited members. Note that getDeclaredFields() method returns also private methods. So given that you navigate the whole superclass hierarchy you will include all private fields declared in the superclasses, and those don&#39;t get inherited.

A simple filter with a Modifier.isPublic || Modifier.isProtected predicate would do:

